# Linear slew has an exact spec: slew=X means X seconds are needed for a change
# of 1 V (0.1 engine units). slew=1.0 -> rate 0.1/s -> at tickrate 100 the step
# per tick is (0.1/1.0)/100 = 0.001. The output ramps from 0 toward a stepped
# input of 0.05, +0.001 each tick, reaching 0.05 after 50 ticks.
# (Output starts at 0 on load.)
tickrate 100
patch <<<
[slew]
    input  = I1
    slew   = 1.0
    linear = O1
>>>
@0 set I1 0.05
@0 expect O1 0.001 tol 1e-6
@4 expect O1 0.005 tol 1e-6
@9 expect O1 0.010 tol 1e-6
@24 expect O1 0.025 tol 1e-6
@49 expect O1 0.050 tol 1e-6
@50 expect O1 0.050 tol 1e-6
@60 expect O1 0.050 tol 1e-6
